WEBVTT

00:02.001 --> 00:05.403
<i>Now the story of a wealthy family</i>
<i>who lost everything...</i>

00:05.505 --> 00:07.496
<i>and the one son</i>
<i>who had no choice...</i>

00:07.607 --> 00:09.598
<i>but to keep them all together.</i>

00:15.115 --> 00:16.742
<i>It's</i> Arrested Development.

00:19.052 --> 00:21.282
<i>Michael was surprised to find the house...</i>

00:21.388 --> 00:23.856
<i>still a mess a week</i>
<i>after the fumigation.</i>

00:23.957 --> 00:28.690
You still haven't put this stuff back yet?
You've got to be the laziest person in the world.

00:28.795 --> 00:31.889
If you weren't all the way on the other side
of the room, I'd slap your face.

00:31.998 --> 00:35.434
- I asked you to clean this up.
- Yeah, and you also asked me
to call the fumigators...

00:35.535 --> 00:37.696
and you haven't even thanked me
for doing that.

00:37.804 --> 00:40.967
<i>Michael</i> had <i>asked her</i>
<i>to do this, but that was long before...</i>

00:41.074 --> 00:43.634
<i>he began hiding his fugitive father</i>
<i>in the attic.</i>

00:43.743 --> 00:47.611
What? Uh- Oh, God.

00:47.714 --> 00:50.706
Polly, cover your mouth!

00:50.817 --> 00:54.719
<i>Luckily, Michael was notified in time.</i>

00:54.821 --> 00:58.120
<i>Well, we had a deal, you know. I'd pay</i>
<i>for everything, and you'd clean the house.</i>

00:58.224 --> 01:01.057
- And you've only done it once.
- <i>She hadn't even done it that time...</i>

01:01.161 --> 01:04.289
<i>but instead, intercepted</i>
<i>her mother's housekeeper...</i>

01:04.397 --> 01:06.763
- <i>as she was arriving for work.</i>
- <i>Can I take you the rest of the way?</i>

01:06.866 --> 01:11.394
- <i>Mrs.</i>- <i>Mrs.</i>-
- Oh, I have to make one quick stop first.

01:11.504 --> 01:15.998
<i>Almost done. Yours or mister's?</i>

01:16.109 --> 01:18.134
Mister's.

01:18.244 --> 01:21.077
<i>Lupe never accepted a ride from Lindsay again.</i>

01:21.181 --> 01:25.140
<i>Well, I'm sorry, Michael,</i>
<i>but Tobias moving out hasn't been easy.</i>

01:25.251 --> 01:27.276
For any of us.

01:27.387 --> 01:29.617
You didn't even notice he'd gone,
did you?

01:29.722 --> 01:31.917
I did notice we'd stopped TiVoing
<i>The Christopher Lowell Show.</i>

01:32.025 --> 01:35.654
- What happened?
- <i>I tried to give it one last chance.</i>

01:35.762 --> 01:38.822
- Like what you see?
- <i>I've been looking for those.</i>

01:38.932 --> 01:41.594
- You're gonna stretch them out.
- That's all you can say?

01:41.701 --> 01:44.932
Well, excuse me for liking the way
they shape my junk.

01:45.038 --> 01:47.438
I don't know why, but that's it.

01:47.540 --> 01:51.340
You can pack your junk
and get out.

01:51.444 --> 01:54.004
You're kicking me out?
At the beginning of pilot season?

01:54.114 --> 01:58.483
You're not gonna make it as an actor,
and we're not gonna make it as a couple.

01:58.585 --> 02:01.611
<i>With nowhere to go,</i>
<i>Tobias went to the studio...</i>

02:01.721 --> 02:05.054
<i>where he'd occasionally worked</i>
<i>as a security guard and took up residence...</i>

02:05.158 --> 02:09.116
<i>in the apartment of Detective Frank Wrench,</i>
<i>on the set of the television show...</i>

02:09.229 --> 02:11.356
Wrench.

02:11.464 --> 02:14.490
<i>I'm really sorry to hear that.</i>
<i>How's Maeby taking it?</i>

02:14.601 --> 02:18.196
- Well, she's really hard to read.
- You haven't told her yet.

02:18.304 --> 02:20.864
Well, she was so excited the hot water
in the shower was lasting longer.

02:20.974 --> 02:23.807
How could I have the heart to tell her
it's because her father moved out?

02:23.910 --> 02:27.141
Tobias moved out?

02:27.247 --> 02:30.978
- Did he take the good video camera with him?
- <i>That's touching.</i>

02:31.084 --> 02:34.178
- What do you need the camera for?
- I'm making a magic video.

02:34.287 --> 02:36.915
I'm gonna tape myself
doing tricks around the office.

02:37.023 --> 02:41.255
I'm calling it <i>Tricks</i>-
Let me finish- <i>around the Office.</i>

02:41.361 --> 02:43.852
I figured out a way to
make money while I'm working.

02:43.963 --> 02:47.228
That <i>is</i> what we call working. Something
you might wanna try next time you're at the office.

02:47.333 --> 02:51.030
<i>You've been missing things lately.</i>
<i>I'm gettin'real tired of it.</i>

02:51.137 --> 02:53.731
<i>Incidentally, today we're having a big vote</i>
<i>on that building renovation.</i>

02:53.840 --> 02:56.673
- I need you there to help me vote it in.
- Fine. I'll vote...

02:56.776 --> 02:58.676
as long as
you give me the camera.

02:58.778 --> 03:01.611
I think we all know
that George Michael was using it last.

03:01.714 --> 03:05.810
<i>A fact the family had discovered</i>
<i>when they'd gathered to watch a home video.</i>

03:05.919 --> 03:09.252
Was that a 40th anniversary party, huh?
Didn't cost us a thing.

03:09.355 --> 03:12.290
Is that Qusay Hussein
at the omelet bar?

03:12.392 --> 03:15.452
Look at this. If these guys move,
they don't get paid.

03:17.197 --> 03:20.098
<i>It seems that as a 13-year-old,</i>
<i>George Michael had been...</i>

03:20.200 --> 03:22.862
<i>heavily influenced</i>
<i>by the</i> Star Wars <i>films...</i>

03:22.969 --> 03:26.461
<i>and had endeavored to</i>
<i>re-create his favorite moments.</i>

03:26.573 --> 03:29.736
- You're not my father! You'll never be!
- I spent $2.1 million...

03:29.842 --> 03:32.310
<i>of good company money</i>
<i>and end up with this?</i>

03:32.412 --> 03:34.710
<i>You cut off my hand!</i>
<i>Worth every penny.</i>

03:34.814 --> 03:38.306
Even you have to admit that
that was the lamest thing ever put on tape.

03:38.418 --> 03:41.683
<i>Not so. Buster</i>
<i>had once videotaped himself...</i>

03:41.788 --> 03:45.656
<i>re-creating moments from his</i>
<i>then favorite film,</i> Chicago.

03:45.758 --> 03:50.388
<i>He also liked</i> Star Wars.

03:52.332 --> 03:55.301
His self-esteem is low enough as it is,
and I have no idea why.

03:55.401 --> 03:58.564
<i>I mean, he's such a great kid, and</i>
<i>everybody loves him. He's George Michael!</i>

03:58.671 --> 04:03.768
<i>Truthfully, that's why I'm not that crazy</i>
<i>about that Ann, but he'll move on.</i>

04:03.876 --> 04:07.812
Unless he knocks her up like you did
with his mother. Plus, she's religious.

04:07.914 --> 04:10.906
If that one gets pregnant,
it stays pregnant.

04:11.017 --> 04:14.851
Believe me. I dated a chick like that
once in high school.

04:14.954 --> 04:17.081
No, I didn't.

04:17.190 --> 04:20.956
<i>I gotta work</i>
<i>on that boy's self-esteem.</i>

04:21.060 --> 04:24.325
<i>Michael went to do so,</i>
<i>only to hear Ann beating him to it.</i>

04:24.430 --> 04:26.489
- <i>I want you to do it.</i>
- <i>I don't think I'm ready.</i>

04:26.599 --> 04:28.863
- <i>Of course you are.</i>
- <i>I'm gonna lose it before I start.</i>

04:28.968 --> 04:31.300
Don't start!

04:31.404 --> 04:35.773
Smoking. It's a killer. That Sammy Davis Jr.
Should still be performing.

04:35.875 --> 04:38.867
- What's going on?
- Ann thinks I should run
for student body president.

04:38.978 --> 04:41.446
- That's a great idea.
- Well, I don't have a chance.

04:41.547 --> 04:44.482
- They only vote for the cool kids.
- But everyone loves you.

04:44.584 --> 04:46.848
You are George Michael!
Who's cooler than you?

04:49.255 --> 04:51.485
Plus, you would be following
in your old man's footsteps.

04:51.591 --> 04:53.684
- You were student body president?
- Oh-ho.

04:53.793 --> 04:56.125
- It was close.
- So you lost.

04:56.229 --> 04:57.992
- Who remembers?
- I know I would remember.

04:58.097 --> 05:00.156
Ann, if my dad says
that he won, then he won.

05:00.266 --> 05:02.700
<i>Didn't say I won.</i>
<i>Said I can't remember.</i>

05:02.802 --> 05:07.136
But now that we're thinking about it, I seem
to remember the other guy won the title...

05:07.240 --> 05:10.209
although there were plenty in the school
who wanted to overturn the decision.

05:10.310 --> 05:14.838
I said, "Let's- Do not- Let's not
put the school through that."

05:14.947 --> 05:17.415
Haven't thought about that for years.
Good memory.

05:17.517 --> 05:21.476
<i>Well, anyway, I'll help you run your campaign</i>
<i>and make your commercial for election day.</i>

05:21.587 --> 05:24.112
Well, that's great.
The important thing is...

05:24.223 --> 05:29.923
to raise the old self-esteem and not
to rush a physical relationship.

05:30.029 --> 05:33.362
- Those are really the two important things.
- <i>No. We're both waiting.</i>

05:33.466 --> 05:37.835
- Good.
- And then that first time,
after waiting and waiting-

05:37.937 --> 05:41.202
It's gonna be so awesome, because it's not
just gonna be my love and George Michael's...

05:41.307 --> 05:43.275
but God's love as well.

05:43.376 --> 05:47.005
- God, it's gonna be incredible.
- <i>All right. I'll do it. I'm in.</i>

05:47.113 --> 05:49.343
- Campaign?
- I'm pumped.

05:49.449 --> 05:52.543
<i>As George Michael was</i>
<i>on the path to higher self-esteem...</i>

05:52.652 --> 05:55.485
<i>Buster was losing</i>
<i>what little he had.</i>

05:55.588 --> 05:57.522
I can't put the aorta in
with this thing.

05:57.623 --> 06:00.490
<i>Oh, stop complaining.</i>

06:00.593 --> 06:04.859
- Buster!
- I'm sorry I'm an inconvenience to you, Mother.

06:04.964 --> 06:09.594
Oh, God! Oh, God! Oh!

