George Sr. Had come to...

13:35.314 --> 13:39.011
<i>in the attic, and perhaps it was the effect</i>
<i>oflosing his one friend</i>-

13:39.118 --> 13:42.144
- Polly?
- <i>or the lingering effects of the fumigation</i>-

13:42.254 --> 13:45.087
<i>or perhaps it really was</i>
<i>divine intervention</i>-

13:45.191 --> 13:48.991
<i>but he'd had a profound realization.</i>

13:52.164 --> 13:55.725
<i>Unfortunately, the timing</i>
<i>of the enlightenment wasn't ideal for Michael.</i>

13:55.835 --> 13:59.896
- That's why I need your help.
- "Our Heavenly Father let his son die...

14:00.005 --> 14:02.405
so that our sins
could be absolved."

14:02.508 --> 14:06.569
- Great. So you're a Christian now.
- "We must all seek forgiveness."

14:06.679 --> 14:09.170
Well, I'll call the warden for you.
You can ask him yourself.

14:09.281 --> 14:14.742
Well, I think that's for fresh crimes.
Besides, you've always tried to lead a clean life.

14:14.854 --> 14:20.190
You and Gob were like
those biblical brothers, Gallant and, um-

14:20.292 --> 14:22.283
"Goofuth."

14:22.394 --> 14:25.625
<i>Michael realized he</i> had <i>lived like Gallant...</i>

14:25.731 --> 14:28.291
<i>and ifhe wanted</i>
<i>to help his son's election...</i>

14:28.400 --> 14:30.527
<i>he would have to find...</i>
<i>Goofuth.</i>

14:30.636 --> 14:33.230
- Been lookin' all over for you, pal.
- If you came to grovel...

14:33.339 --> 14:35.307
for the job of president,
you're too late.

14:35.407 --> 14:40.401
- My brother already fired me.
- Listen, I'm really sorry that I got upset with you...

14:40.512 --> 14:43.916
you know, and I never meant to, um-
I didn't even mean to fire you.

14:43.916 --> 14:45.941
You know, and I never meant to, um-
I didn't even mean to fire you.

14:46.051 --> 14:50.420
You know? I just got so frustrated,
and, Gob, you are my brother.

14:50.522 --> 14:54.253
- Of course I'm gonna support you.
- Well...

14:54.360 --> 14:56.419
now I feel bad for firing you.

14:56.528 --> 14:59.964
Listen, George Michael is running
for student body president...

15:00.065 --> 15:01.965
and I have a feeling
he's gonna get slaughtered.

15:02.067 --> 15:05.002
The guy he's running against
is basically a young you.

15:05.104 --> 15:10.406
Wow. It won't be easy
to win a race against myself.

15:10.509 --> 15:13.342
- Of course, if anyone can do it, I can.
- That's right.

15:13.445 --> 15:16.937
- I wish I was 15 years younger.
- He doesn't need to beat him.

15:17.049 --> 15:20.507
- He just needs to beat the Indian kid.
- If I do this, you'll rehire me?

15:20.619 --> 15:23.383
- Of course I will.
- The mere fact that you think you can...

15:23.489 --> 15:26.617
says to me
that I shouldn't let you.

15:26.725 --> 15:30.923
Course,
we both need the work.

15:31.030 --> 15:32.998
Robot'll get it.

15:33.098 --> 15:35.692
Where the hell is my maid?
Robot!

15:35.801 --> 15:39.259
<i>But the robot was busy elsewhere.</i>

15:42.408 --> 15:46.003
What do you expect, Mother? I'm half machine!

15:47.479 --> 15:50.073
I'm a monster!

15:58.557 --> 16:01.651
<i>Michael brought Gob in</i>
<i>to consult on his son's campaign.</i>

16:01.760 --> 16:04.991
Focus on the video and shy away
from the virgin thing.

16:05.097 --> 16:07.964
Oh, we should definitely
sacrifice the whole virgin thing.

16:08.067 --> 16:10.058
<i>And I got the perfect way.</i>

16:10.169 --> 16:14.299
We hand out rubbers that say,
"We salute George Michael."

16:14.406 --> 16:17.500
- We're not supposed to have help.
- I don't wanna make Steve look bad.

16:17.609 --> 16:20.669
Yeah, I just don't want my son to be
embarrassed up there. Let's not play too dirty.

16:20.779 --> 16:24.579
- Uh, good point, two percent.
- Two percent, huh? Is that how little I lost by?

16:24.683 --> 16:26.651
- Lost by? That's all you got.
- Not really important.

16:26.752 --> 16:30.654
<i>Well, if your son wants more than two percent,</i>
<i>he's gonna have to go after Steve Holt.</i>

16:30.756 --> 16:34.487
<i>So I want you to tell me every awful rumor</i>
<i>you've ever heard about this kid.</i>

16:34.593 --> 16:37.027
I can't support this,
and neither can the Christian kids...

16:37.129 --> 16:39.825
- that were gonna make you president.
- Uh-

16:39.932 --> 16:42.833
<i>Ann? I think</i>
<i>she's really upset about this.</i>

16:42.935 --> 16:46.268
She'll forgive ya.
You're George Michael.

16:46.372 --> 16:49.273
<i>Meanwhile...</i>

16:49.375 --> 16:51.343
<i>Maeby was meeting</i>
<i>her new singing nanny.</i>

16:51.443 --> 16:54.207
Now. Take your Fun-fun.

16:54.313 --> 16:58.682
This is my mom's, and it's fen-phen,
and it's been banned by the F.D.A.

16:58.784 --> 17:03.278
Oh! Well.
You should always read the label

17:03.389 --> 17:06.915
<i>You should always read it well</i>
<i>in the most delicious way</i>

17:07.026 --> 17:09.085
- Mr. Fingerbottom?
- Mrs.

17:09.194 --> 17:11.424
<i>Right. Mrs.</i>
<i>I should really get going.</i>

17:11.530 --> 17:15.125
No, no, no, no, no.
Sit back. What's the rush? Please.

17:15.233 --> 17:17.964
I wanna hear about you.
Tell me about your family.

17:18.069 --> 17:22.632
I'm sure wherever your father is right now,
she loves you very, very much.

17:22.741 --> 17:25.767
Not enough to be honest
with me.

17:28.380 --> 17:30.746
<i>And after a few days, Gob was ready...</i>

17:30.849 --> 17:33.079
<i>to unveil</i>
<i>George Michael's new message.</i>

17:33.185 --> 17:35.983
<i>Drought, starvation</i>-

17:36.088 --> 17:40.286
These are the things my family
has had to deal with for generations...

17:40.392 --> 17:43.327
although, fortunately,
not since we moved to Corona del Mar.

17:43.429 --> 17:47.126
<i>Go home, you terrorist!</i>

17:47.232 --> 17:49.962
How stupid do you have to be
to say something like that?

17:50.069 --> 17:53.470
- You're not wanted here!
- Gob.

17:53.572 --> 17:56.439
- Michael.
- You got George Michael's tape?

17:56.542 --> 18:00.444
Yeah. I gave it to the tech guy.
Don't worry. It's very tastefully done.

18:00.546 --> 18:03.447
Sure you didn't make that video in a cave?

18:03.549 --> 18:06.279
<i>- Perennial candidate Steve Holt!</i>
<i>- Soon it was time...</i>

18:06.385 --> 18:08.444
<i>for Steve Holt to play his video...</i>

18:08.554 --> 18:11.819
<i>which had been produced</i>
<i>by his new campaign manager, Ann Veal.</i>

18:11.924 --> 18:16.156
- Hi. I'm Steve Holt.
<i>- Evil!</i>

18:16.261 --> 18:19.492
This kid's popular?

18:19.598 --> 18:22.123
Looks like a chick I did
once in high school.

18:22.234 --> 18:24.293
Get a haircut!

18:24.403 --> 18:27.429
Recently, I've been dealing with the fact
that I've never known my father...

18:27.539 --> 18:31.134
<i>but I finally found a new Father.</i>

18:31.243 --> 18:34.110
You're probably wondering
what these footsteps are.

18:34.213 --> 18:39.515
Well, this is my second take. It's kind of
like a second chance at making good.

18:42.287 --> 18:45.518
<i>Yeah. Okay. We need</i>
<i>to pull the videotape.</i>

18:45.624 --> 18:47.990
- My tape?
- Why?
- I've made a huge mistake.

18:48.093 --> 18:52.029
<i>But it was too late</i>
<i>to do anything about it.</i>

18:52.131 --> 18:56.500
Steve Holt is a bastard.
He doesn't even know who his real father is.

18:56.602 --> 19:01.335
What else don't we know
about Steve Holt?

19:01.440 --> 19:04.705
George Michael Bluth
is a cool guy.

19:04.810 --> 19:08.075
His dad is a powerful executive
working for this man.

19:08.180 --> 19:12.082
The girls like him just fine.
Young and old. It doesn't matter.

19:12.184 --> 19:15.244
- In the dark.
- That's why you had me do that?

19:15.354 --> 19:18.585
<i>George Michael</i>
<i>had never been more embarrassed.</i>

19:18.690 --> 19:21.352
<i>Until this part.</i>

19:21.460 --> 19:23.519
I couldn't find another tape.

19:29.801 --> 19:32.827
I like Steve's more.

19:32.938 --> 19:35.998
Guess I underestimated
the religious vote.

19:36.108 --> 19:39.271
- So Steve won?
- No. Steve dropped out of the race.

19:39.378 --> 19:41.938
He says he wants to spend some time
trying to find his real father.

19:42.047 --> 19:45.346
Rav Nadir, the Indian kid,
he got 97% of the vote.

19:45.450 --> 19:50.046
Well, that leaves three percent.
You did better than I did when I ran.

19:50.155 --> 19:52.851
I tied with Bart Simpson
and "School Sucks."

19:52.958 --> 19:54.983
I'm really sorry, buddy.
Believe it or not, I did this...

19:55.093 --> 19:57.425
because I didn't want you
to feel bad about yourself.

19:57.529 --> 20:00.259
Hey, it's Star Dork.

20:00.365 --> 20:03.391
Hey, he knows you now.
I'm really sorry, buddy.

20:03.502 --> 20:07.438
It's just a drag. I mean, I'm pretty sure
my girlfriend's gone forever...

20:07.539 --> 20:09.564
and I never wanted
to do this in the first place.

20:09.675 --> 20:15.079
George Michael, was that really you
doing those lightsaber moves?

20:15.180 --> 20:18.377
- You were incredible.
- I've only gotten better.

20:18.483 --> 20:21.077
You're still doin' that?

20:21.186 --> 20:25.953
<i>So, you wanna grab a curtain rod</i>
<i>and go over to my place?</i>

20:26.058 --> 20:29.118
Wow. I'd love that.
Thanks, Ann.

20:29.228 --> 20:32.322
You really make me
feel good about myself.

20:35.067 --> 20:39.299
Gotta do something
about that kid's self-esteem.

20:39.404 --> 20:41.838
<i>On the next</i> Arrested Development.

20:44.042 --> 20:46.738
Yoo-hoo!
I'll take you the rest of the way!

20:46.845 --> 20:50.611
<i>Lucille finds a housekeeper</i>
<i>that she won't lose her son to.</i>

20:50.716 --> 20:55.551
Always keep from crying
even though your heart is dying

21:01.560 --> 21:04.427
<i>And Steve Holt finally</i>
<i>tracks down his real father.</i>

21:04.529 --> 21:06.929
I've been wonderin'
my whole life who he is-

21:07.032 --> 21:09.967
a scientist,
a doctor, a senator?

21:10.068 --> 21:13.128
Well, we got some bad news.

21:13.238 --> 21:17.766
Wow. Is that what's
gonna happen to my hair?

